The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Prague, Oct. 17: Ashok Leyland has acquired the Avia truck business unit, a European vehicle manufacturer, at an estimated cost of around $35 million. Started as an aircraft and engine manufacturer in 1919, Avia diversified later into trucks and signed licence agreement with Renault in 1967. In 1995, Avia was acquired by Daewoo Motor Corporation with a majority share. Ashok Leyland has become the first Indian company to have a truck manufacturing unit in Europe.

 Mumbai, Oct. 17: The Reserve Bank has raised the ceiling for home loans offered by the urban cooperative banks (UCBs) to Rs 25 lakh from Rs 15 lakh. An RBI release, however, said that home loans beyond Rs 15 lakh by UCBs will hereafter not be treated as priority sector lending.

 Mumbai, Oct. 17: GTL Ltd has bought Genesis Consultancy, a UK-based network management and professional services company, in an all-cash deal of $9 million (Rs 40.50 crore). GTL will acquire Genesis through IGTL Solutions (UK). 

 Mumbai, Oct. 17: General Motors (GM) will launch the Chevrolet-UVA in two months, besides rolling out its compact passenger vehicle Spark in the first half of 2007.

 New Delhi, Oct. 17: The telecom subscribers in the country increased by 5.9 million in September and the overall teledensity improved to 15.1 per cent from 14.6 per cent in August 2006.




